"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-olympic-tennis-rules-everything-you-need-to-know-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"We are only days away from the 2024 Summer Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 66, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 60, \"end\": 65, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999926510554, \"rank\": 7.348986598051173e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 27, thetennistournament will begin, featuring a star-studded cast of participants.\", \"from\": 67, \"to\": 157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, the competition will take place on clay at Stade Roland Garros in Paris, France, home of theFrench Open.\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 236, \"end\": 241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999926510554, \"rank\": 7.348986598051173e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 243, \"end\": 249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8735334757263854, \"rank\": 0.13838900090243808, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the most famous venues in the world, it is a fitting establishment for what should be an exciting atmosphere.\", \"from\": 275, \"to\": 390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Location aside, how does Olympic tennis compare to ATP/WTA rules and formatting we are accustomed to (if at all)?\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 505, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Are there differences between the transnational and conventional playing/viewing experience?\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's everything you need to know about the upcoming Olympic tennis competition before the festivities in Paris begin.\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 707, \"end\": 712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999926510554, \"rank\": 7.348986598051173e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic tennis has five events -- men's/women's singles/doubles, and mixed doubles.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The size of each respective draw is listed as follows:  Olympic Tournament  Size of Field  Women's singles  64  Men's singles  64  Women's doubles  32  Men's doubles  32  Mixed doubles  16  A best-of-three-set structure determines an Olympic tennis match.\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 1060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly to the ATP/WTA scoring system, a traditional tiebreak is played to seven points, though you must win by two.\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1078, \"end\": 1081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Association_of_Tennis_Professionals\", \"score\": 0.8854667110060981, \"rank\": 0.12934782249339172, \"text\": \"ATP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Association_of_Tennis_Professionals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Association_of_Tennis_Professionals\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One player starts the conclusive game with a service.\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterward, the contestants alternate after every two serves.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In tennis, a cumulative point-based method typically determines a player's ranking.\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alas, the outcome of the Olympics does not factor into the hierarchy, making it more about having pride in your native country than anything.\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Per the International Tennis Federation (ITF), one must fulfill\\u00c2specific requirements\\u00c2\\u00a0to partake in theOlympics.\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1531, \"end\": 1562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Tennis_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Tennis Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Tennis_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Tennis_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Various prerequisites spanning from age, previous participation and being in \\\"good standing\\\" with the governing bodies of the sport weigh into eligibility.\\u00c2  Qualifying for the global tournament is a rigorous process and no easy feat.\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, a country can not have more than 12 representatives (six men and six women) across the five competitions.\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nonetheless, the host nation (in this case, France) gets one walk-on per contest.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2031, \"end\": 2037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8735334757263854, \"rank\": 0.13838900090243808, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overall, not much separates an Olympic tennis outing from a standard affair.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"